column4: In the Italian Dept., University of Warwick
Graduate student in the Department of History at the University of Connecticut.
I research on Medieval and Renaissance Italian Literature, particularly Petrarch's views on monasticism and church reform.
Assistant Professor of German, University of Missouri, Columbia
Teacher, calligrapher. I live in Italy.
I'm a German MA student at the University of Missouri - Columbia
Student of Professor Stevens' "History of the Book" class
Graphic designer and collector of early grammatical works
I'm a student of the history of conjuring and magic. I also collect early books on the subject.
